    from urllib import error

url = 'https://www.google.com/search?q=python'

def download(url,retries = 3):
    resp = None
    try:
        resp = request.urlopen(url)
    except error.HTTPError as e:
        if 500 <= e.code < 600 and retries > 0:
            return download(url,retries-1)
        else:
            print(e.code)
            print(e.reason)
            print(e.headers)
    return resp

download(url)

    In [113]:
    from urllib import error

url = 'https://www.google.com/search?q=python'
agent = {'user-agent':'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/72.0.3626.119 Safari/537.36'}

def download(url,retries = 3):
    resp = None
    req = request.Request(url,headers=agent)
    
    try:
        resp = request.urlopen(req)
    except error.HTTPError as e:
        if 500 <= e.code < 600 and retries > 0:
            return download(url,retries-1)
        else:
            print(e.code)
            print(e.reason)
            print(e.headers)
    return resp

html = download(url)

    from urllib import error

url = 'https://www.google.com/search?q=python'
agent = {'user-agent':'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/72.0.3626.119 Safari/537.36'}

def download(url,param, retries = 3):
    resp = None
    try:
        resp = requests.get(url,params=param, headers=agent)
        resp.raise_for_status() # error check
    except requests.exceptions.HTTPError as e:
        if 500 <= e.code < 600 and retries > 0:
            return download(url,retries-1)
        else:
            print(e.code)
            print(e.reason)
            print(e.headers)
            print(resp.request.headers)
            
    return resp
